line_1: Dolphins, by all the liquid Realms rever'd,
line_2: Command the Seas, and rule the floating Herd.

line_1: By Terror guarded, and by kings rever'd:
line_2: Th' inviolable dame majestic rear'd,

line_1: Who blest in life, and were in death rever'd,
line_2: There many a sage and patriot appear'd,

line_1: O'er her pale cheek; for there the rose revered
line_2: The silent Muses who her presence feared:

line_1: He lived unequalled, died revered,
line_2: To every bird was Hawk endeared;

line_1: Proclaim the theme, by Sage, by Fool rever'd;
line_2: 'Tis Nature speaks, and Nature will be heard.

line_1: The servants of the Devil are rever'd,
line_2: And Bishops pull the Fathers by the beard.

line_1: Thus proud prerogative, not much rever'd,
line_2: Is seldom felt, though sometimes seen and heard;

line_1: By every heart rever'd.
line_2: In highest heaven is rear'd,

line_1: On Tiber's banks, by sacred priests rever'd,
line_2: Where in the days of old a god appear'd:

line_1: I come, she said, oh! most rever'd,
line_2: Accept the offering I've prepar'd;

line_1: She sung, that names thro' time rever'd,
line_2: Thro' toils and death had madly err'd;

line_1: Wealth may be courted, wisdom be rever'd,
line_2: And beauty prais'd, and brutal strength be fear'd;

line_1: That virtue was at all rever'd.
line_2: Since I was hatch'd, I never heard,

line_1: Oh! thou lov'd excellence revered,
line_2: So honor'd, and where known endeared;

line_1: Excess in Youth made Scipio less rever'd:
line_2: And Cato dying seem'd to own, He fear'd.

line_1: Taught 'em how Clemency made Pow'r rever'd;
line_2: And that the Prince Belov'd was truly Fear'd.

line_1: For warriors, and for wits rever'd;
line_2: Of Greece, as you have often heard,

line_1: (The only Planets I rever'd)
line_2: Ev'n those Fair Eyes that Planets once appear'd,

line_1: Serv'd from affection, for his worth rever'd:
line_2: By deeds of hospitality endear'd,

line_1: Behold, four Kings in Majesty rever'd,
line_2: With hoary Whiskers and a forky Beard;

line_1: And, for Thy Justice, be Thy Name rever'd.
line_2: So in my Conquest be Thy Might declar'd:

line_1: Remov'd those Pow'rs, whom justly she rever'd,
line_2: There plac'd too soon the flaming Sword appear'd,

line_1: Remov'd those Pow'rs, whom justly she rever'd,
line_2: Adher'd too in their Wreck, and in their Ruin shar'd.

line_1: THOU, most belov'd, most honour'd, most rever'd!
line_2: And blame me not, if by each tye endear'd,
